Sentencas: We evaluated the electrochemical performances of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 (LNFO) and LaNi0.6Co0.4O3 (LNCO) perovskites as cathodes in La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.83Mg0.17O2.(815) (LSGM) electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Evaluation of LaNi0.6M0.4O3 (M = Fe, Co) cathodes in LSGM-electrolyte-supported solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Both samples show excellent chemical compatibility with the LSGM electrolyte up to 900 degrees C, and exhibit small-polaron type electrical conduction with a high conductivity sigma approximate to 510 (430) S.cm(-1) at 800 degrees C and a small activation energy E-e(a) = 54.9 (44.4) meV for LNFO (LNCO).
Titulo: Evaluation of LaNi0.6M0.4O3 (M = Fe, Co) cathodes in LSGM-electrolyte-supported solid-oxide fuel cells

Titulo: Evaluation of LaNi0.6M0.4O3 (M = Fe, Co) cathodes in LSGM-electrolyte-supported solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For a single cell composed of LNFO (LNCO) cathode, 300-mu m-thick LSGM electrolyte, and a composite Ni + Gd-doped ceria anode, the maximum power densities reach P-max = 490 (650) and 850 (1015) mW.cm(-2) at 800 and 850 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Evaluation of LaNi0.6M0.4O3 (M = Fe, Co) cathodes in LSGM-electrolyte-supported solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results demonstrated that LNFO and LNCO are promising cathode materials for the IT-SOFCs.
